HEADWORD: malaxator
<hw>mal"ax*a`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that
which, malaxates; esp., a machine for grinding, kneading, or stirring
into a pasty or doughy mass.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

